{"title":"Redshift Sports New Top Shelf Riser Drop Bar: Where BMX Meets Gravel?","link":"https://bikerumor.com/redshift-sports-top-shelf-riser-drop-bar/","date":1712165174000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" alt=\"(Photo/Ron Frazelle)\" /></p>\n<p>The clever minds that brought us the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/redshift-kitchen-sink-handlebar-gravel-exploration-must-have-upgrade/\" target=\"_blank\">Kitchen Sink</a> handlebar and the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-redshift-sports-shockstop-suspension-stem-defies-bumps-expectations/\" target=\"_blank\">ShockStop</a> stem are at it again. Today, <a href=\"https://redshiftsports.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Redshift Sports</a> released their new <a href=\"https://redshiftsports.com/products/top-shelf-handlebar-system\" target=\"_blank\">riser drop bar</a>, the Top Shelf. As you probably guessed, it’s a drop bar that offers two choices of hefty rise, 50mm and 70mm (2″ and 2.75″).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-50-or-70mm-rise-e1712163545649.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"492\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-50-or-70mm-rise-e1712163545649.jpeg\" alt=\"Redshift Top Shelf Handlebar 50 or 70mm rise\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-50-or-70mm-rise-e1712163545649.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-50-or-70mm-rise-e1712163545649-297x122.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-50-or-70mm-rise-e1712163545649-120x49.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-50-or-70mm-rise-e1712163545649-768x315.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>50 or 70 mm rise available. (Photo/Redshift Sports)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-in-action-50mm-rise.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-in-action-50mm-rise.jpeg\" alt=\"Redshift Top Shelf Handlebar in action 50mm rise\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-in-action-50mm-rise.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-in-action-50mm-rise-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-in-action-50mm-rise-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-in-action-50mm-rise-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-in-action-50mm-rise-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-in-action-50mm-rise-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Redshift Sports)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Comfortable drop bars are something that we are seeing more and more lately. With their shorter reaches, back sweeps, and shallower drops some companies claim that their bars offer “all-day comfort”. But a drop bar with a 70mm rise raises it up a notch and shows Redshift’s commitment to comfyness. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The bar will be great for any drop-bar activity, on the road, in the gravel, out bikepacking, or commuting – essentially anyone on a drop bar bike looking for a higher riding position.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Redshift Top Shelf Retail and Key Features</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-front-e1712163874272.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"512\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-front-e1712163874272.jpeg\" alt=\"Redshift Top Shelf Handlebar front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-front-e1712163874272.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-front-e1712163874272-297x119.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-front-e1712163874272-120x48.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-front-e1712163874272-768x307.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Ron Frazelle)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $139 (price as tested)</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key</strong> <strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Ultra-comfortable, upright, and relaxed riding position without the need for a highly angled stem or long steerer tube.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lots of room to mount accessories and bags</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Double-bar construction means bags are super secure</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebars-specs-e1712163908142.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"630\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebars-specs-e1712163908142.jpeg\" alt=\"Redshift Top Shelf Handlebars specs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebars-specs-e1712163908142.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebars-specs-e1712163908142-297x156.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebars-specs-e1712163908142-120x63.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebars-specs-e1712163908142-768x403.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Redshift Sports)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Details:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Perfect for road, gravel, bikepacking, and commuting</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rise: 50 or 70mm </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Storage: The double-bar construction provides room for all of your bar-mounted accouterments</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Control: The rise of the bar brings the drops closer, allowing for more use of the drops for more control</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Backsweep: 7-degrees of back sweep</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Flare: 25-degrees of flare</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Wide: Available in 44, 47, and 50cm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lifetime Warranty, 90 risk-free trial, free shipping in the US, UK, EU, and CAN</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>First Impressions </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-backsweep.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-backsweep.jpeg\" alt=\"Redshift Top Shelf Handlebar backsweep\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-backsweep.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-backsweep-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-backsweep-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-backsweep-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-backsweep-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-backsweep-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Ron Frazelle)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I received the bar with a 50mm rise, and 47cm width. I would normally be on at least a 50cm width, but thought I’d try a little narrower with the amount of rise that the bar has. The 6061 T6 aluminum Top Shelf bar has a nice 7-degree back sweep, which I prefer in my drop bars. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-actual-weight.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"964\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-actual-weight.jpeg\" alt=\"Redshift Top Shelf Handlebar actual weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-actual-weight.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-actual-weight-297x224.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-actual-weight-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-actual-weight-768x578.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Ron Frazelle)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 25-degree flare is more than ample for me. it has a short reach and a shallow drop, so getting into and staying in the drops will be more comfortable. The actual weight of the Top Shelf in the 47cm size came in a gram less (508g) than the claimed weight (509g)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-double-bar-construction.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-double-bar-construction.jpeg\" alt=\"Redshift Top Shelf Handlebar double bar construction\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-double-bar-construction.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-double-bar-construction-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-double-bar-construction-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-double-bar-construction-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-double-bar-construction-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-double-bar-construction-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Ron Frazelle)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The unique feature that stood out on this bar when I opened the box, was the flat upper bar, or I guess the double bar construction. I’m sure it adds a bit of weight compared to just having the bar rise without the second bar.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-short-reach-shallow-drop.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-short-reach-shallow-drop.jpeg\" alt=\"Redshift Top Shelf Handlebar short reach, shallow drop\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-short-reach-shallow-drop.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-short-reach-shallow-drop-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-short-reach-shallow-drop-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-short-reach-shallow-drop-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-short-reach-shallow-drop-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Redshift-Top-Shelf-Handlebar-short-reach-shallow-drop-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Short reach and shallow drops are my jam! (Photo/Ron Frazelle)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But the upper bar adds the real estate to add bags, electronics, and other stuff, which will be awesome. Matter of fact, Redshift plans on releasing a custom-fitted bag this summer that fits this bar. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you combine this bar with the Redshift Cruise Control Top and Bottom Grips, you are almost guaranteed a comfortable hand position anywhere on the bar. I’m going to skip that step and wrap the bars traditionally. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>I’m looking forward to spending the Spring on these bars. Stay tuned here for the full review. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out all of the neat products Redshift has to offer by hitting the link below. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://redshiftsports.com/\" target=\"_blank\">RedshiftSports.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/redshift-sports-top-shelf-riser-drop-bar/\">Redshift Sports New Top Shelf Riser Drop Bar: Where BMX Meets Gravel?</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"67c714efe0c936d4b173b5e266d36fbe1f6c1c1b65b3d58f1c2deea5de1e7409","category":"Cycling"}